-- Canada Home Prices Gain for the 15th Straight Month, Teranet Data Shows
-- B y   A l e x a n d r e   D e s l o n g c h a m p s
-- 2010-09-29T13:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-29/canada-home-prices-gain-for-the-15th-straight-month-teranet-data-shows.html
Canadian home prices posted their
15th straight gain in July, the longest streak since 2006, the
 Teranet-National Bank  Composite House Price Index showed.  Prices rose 0.5 percent  during the month , led by Ottawa’s
1.5 percent gain and Toronto’s 1.2 percent increase, according
to a report released today by National Bank Financial.  On an  annual basis , prices rose 12.4 percent, led by gains
in Toronto and Vancouver.  The index has tracked home-price changes in six Canadian
cities -- Halifax, Montreal, Ottawa, Toronto, Calgary and
Vancouver -- since February 2000.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alexandre Deslongchamps  in Ottawa at 
 adeslongcham@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Wellisz at 
 cwellisz@bloomberg.net ;
